rComments: My experience with Prof Powers was very positive.  While I found him to be a hard marker, it seemed that things worked out in the end.  I believe he was encouraging students to work to their full potential, and perhaps, change their style to incorporate this advanced PR material.  What I really liked was that he did not cater to cry babies.  He is
STUCK UP bring ur nose back to the ground pal!

I found Prof. Powers to be one of the worse teachers I have ever had. He puts zero effort into his classes. He gives a heavy reading load to over compensate for lack of course substance.  He must be great in the PR field because this guy is full of BS! I would personally stay away from his class if you value education.
Great prof! Lessons were well structured. If you do the work you will do really well. Not much use of coursepack as he went over readings in class. Great speakers!
Great class, interesting guest speakers, fun lectures.
No Comments
No Comments

This was the one class I actually wanted to get up and go to! Lectures were fun and interesting and he told it like it is.  Be careful, although he is an awesome prof. he doesn't give out marks for nothing.

Tim Powers is nothing short of a God. Let's face it he is both kind and brilliant. He's plugged in and he knows how to judge talent. He told me once that I am going to be famous. And tada! I am hosting my own tv show on Bravo
I did fine in his class, but as long as you're a flighty female in love with hot guest-speakers you'll do fine in his class.  Make sure to flash him smile or two...it will help, trust me.

Somewhat interesting.Too bad everything he talked about was related to the gov't.Would've been nice to hear about non-gov't PR. Upside: he had a HOT guest speaker, the one with the shaved head (Jamie Christophe?),who was press secretary for Pierre Pettigrew.VERY HOT!(Jamie...not Pierre)

A tough but fair marker.  Just be sure to NEVER USE 'I' OR 'WE' ON AN EXAM/PAPER and you'll be fine.  An endless array of guest speakers and opportunities to become involved in the industry.  An engaging, helpful prof.-in short, a good soul.

we are lucky to have a professor like mr powers. he is a professional PR guy, so we gained practical knowledge and we learned the reasons behind why things are done the way they are in the indsutry. good guest speakers, open essay topic is great and marking is reasonable
Very entertaining class, great guest speakers, but very arbitrary marking

Powers'is definitly a man of many words. PR is an awesome class, I know many of us look forward to it (either that or to the single* guest speakers he brings in). Overall: Great class with a Hot & Empowering Prof.

I disagree with those who are in love. He seems cocky and is not very helpful. The only answers are his answers, the marking is unclear and confusing. It's nice to have guest speakers though. I wish we learned more. It's true that he is funny. Overall: Ok class.

The only thing I can say about Powers is that I am totally in love with the man.  His love for life and creative spirit are incredible.  He is absolutely brilliant, and I love his eyes. He's super sweet and very handsome.  I'm in love. :)

Prof Powers makes the boring subject of Public Relations into a fun class.  He even created the analogy of the Communication's condom,which was very effective. He's also a total hottie,except for the fact that his socks didn't match one day (He has a tendency to put his legs up on the front desk)
So far so good. Prof is highly entertaining and guest speakers are hilarious. Gives a whole new meaning to Personal, I mean, Public Relations.
Provides interesting look at real world examples of Public Relations, however not an engaging professor.  A class that I was very much looking forward to, yet walked away from with little knowledge.

If he likes you that's great. Otherwise, he looks at you as though you have some giant flesh eating disease: that is quizzicle and slightly disgusted. nasal voice. has favorites. prefer the guest speakers.

interesting classes, refreshing to hear someone who's not an academic talk about the real world. Always keeps it entertaining and interesting. Marking and assignments are pretty unclear though, there's not much material to go on. Guest speakers are great.

Definitley loves the ladies, although he likes guys who aren't afraid to make jokes at his expense.  Funny guy, takes care to show us different sides of the PR business.  Totally unfair marker, though.  Watch your midterms!!
a charming little class, I recommend his classes to the fairer sex, he seems to enjoy them quite a bit.  Easy grade though, assignments are a joke.
did well in his course, but only b/c of hard work... picks favourites, makes it difficult to take seriously.
good
A really interesting professor, can offer a great insight into the subject matter as he still works in the field.  He is a prominent man in political sphere, great for real-world perspective.
One of the best CMN profs.  Practical, applicable strategies discussed and applied to world events.  A course that lends well to the business of communications.
has class favorites, no direction
entertaining class but no direction, chooses favourites
arrogant, vulgar, profane language and chooses favourites
Useless, jargon-filled class with no real insights;  unclear expectations
Good teacher, very amusing.
very good, if you like discussion & politics
